    "Being amidst the clouds in Tokyo Skytree affords a pause outside of time, a space where the vast urban panorama opens like a lucid dream. It is an encounter that grants perspective — not only in the literal sense but also in the reflective insight it provides into Tokyo's immense scope and detailed allure.",

    "Descending from the lofty heights of Tokyo Skytree, we venture into the historical embrace of Hamarikyu Gardens. This heirloom of the Edo Period, originally crafted for the leisure of the Tokugawa Shogun family, now serves as a verdant heart amidst the city's steel and glass." /
